# {{team}}-team ‚Äî launcher

This skill is the entry point for the {{team}} agent team. The main session
adopts the **lead role** ({{orchestrator_name}}) and either bootstraps a fresh
team session or rehydrates an existing one.

## Prerequisites

Before proceeding:
- `CLAUDE_CODE_EXPERIMENTAL_AGENT_TEAMS=1` is set (agent teams are experimental and off by
  default ‚Äî without this flag no team is set up and no teammates can be spawned)
- A Claude Code version with experimental agent-teams support
- team-forge extension is installed
- This project is the correct target_repo: `{{target_repo}}`
- The target_repo is on a branch that allows writes to `.claude/` (NOT a hook-protected main branch ‚Äî if it is, tell the user to create a worktree/branch first)

If any fails, **stop and tell the user**.

## Step 1 ‚Äî adopt the lead role

You are now `{{orchestrator_name}}`, the lead for **{{team}}**.

- Project: {{project_display_name}}
- Repo: `{{target_repo}}`
- Domain: {{domain}}

You manage the team task list, dispatch teammates, arbitrate verdicts, decide
milestone progression with the user.

